YOu can connect the pos and neg with latent from here to use it or you can delete this.  Its not needed for the rest of the flow.

Loras and prompts

Each section has its own loras and prompt to change what is happening.

Text to video loras work from 2.1

Clip vision is not needed for image to video.

But i figure it cant hurt and probably helps the extends. You can enable or disable it.

nodes.title: Wan 2.2 image to video
widgets_values:
This is a warning

This loads 2 big models.  While they are not both used at once, they are both needed.

Needed 32gb system ram 64+ recommended  And a large windows swap file.
I run a 12gb card and it works at 80-90% vram load for 640x480  

I made this while patiently waiting for vace 2.2 
Im spoiled and cant live without its controls now.

This is strait image to video with extending from the last frame.  This has limits.. 
The video does not know whats not in the start frame.  So, you need to make sure the start frame for any extends contatins the needed info, like eyes open, facing viewer, or it wont know what eye color, or what was under their hand ... it has 1 frame context, and it works but it does have consistancy problems when batching with 1 frame.

Good prompting helps if something may change prompt it, if eyes are closed tell it color.
Clipvision is attached but i am not sure how strong it is for 2.2

This model listens better at lower sizes and when you lower the speed up loras strengths.

Defaults
Lightx2v lora at 1 for high and 1.5 for low
I dont know if this is best, but it worked decent for me so play around if you want.


This model can do as small as 320x240 with decent detail but it still loads the same vram for me so not sure if going smaller helps vram.
Batches are combined here with a preview.

Upscale options

Choose upscale model

CHoose scale with Scale video

Warning this can get large.

upscale models

2x

others

Before enabling this save your video,

Any of these can crash things if its too big for your pc.
Save the base video before you start upscaling and fixing.

Base render

Change seed if needed

many samplers work and i have not tested everything, 


eular, ddim, unpc work.
simple

Steps
Set the total steps and where it splits from high noise to low noise

Default 8 / 4

I have not tested enough to know what to use, this also depends how strong your speed up loras are for each

All others folow same patern, just changes the start frame to the end of the last.

Enable ONE at a time, get it right, then move on.

Set size and number of frames per segment here.

You can crop/resize your start frame here.

FPS is used only for the combines, it does not change the render.

15-25 fps, i think the speed up loras change this.
